FEATURE_NOTES: A scalable software platform for developing and deploying analytic applications across an enterprise.
Self-Service sandbox (in Vantage) for data exploration.
The parent database (in Vantage) of Data Lab databases, allocating the space, default lab size, default lab expiration, and more.
An engine that automates the selection of the best data movement utility, combined with an interface for copying objects between databases.
Console for managing dual systems, integrated with Teradata Unity and Teradata Data Mover.
Parallel access to data across silos and multiple analytic engines.
Synchronize multiple active Teradata (Vantage) systems to work as one.

BUSINESS_VALUE_DESC: Consulting excellence that leverages experiece and proven patterns
FEATURE_NOTES: Consulting Accelerators are the following collection of features and capabilities that drive consulting: AnalyticOps, Hadoop Migration Accelerator, Advocated Stack, Consumption Analytics, DataDNA, DataOps, Ecosystem Encoded
Self service application for running machine learning algorithms and modeling data on Vantage with no coding.
Create groups of objects based on multi-dimensional data similarity (feature of Vantage Analyst).
Build, train, and evaluate predictive models to maximize business value (feature of Vantage Analyst).
Discover actionable insights in a series of behaviors or events (feature of Vantage Analyst).
Analyze text to uncover sentiment and key terms (feature of Vantage Analyst).
Quickly automate analytic workflow to create repeatable and operationalized process (feature of Vantage Analyst).

An open source package of analytic functions written in Python for execution on Vantage, as well as the cability for developers to write new python programs and execute them in Vantage. The Teradata Python package uses SQLAlchemy and has an interface similar to the Pandas Python library.
The teradataml in-database analytic functions that execute using the Advanced SQL Engine . Available in Vantage 1.1 or later.
The Teradata Python Package (teradataml) uses a DataFrame interface to allow programs written in python to interact directly with objects in Vantage/Teradata Database.

The teradataml library provides an API to access or manipulate a teradataml DataFrame. These functions generate an SQL request to be executed in the Advanced SQL Engine or ML Engine through a Python DB-API connection.
Perform aggregate operations on time series data using APIs to group or resample time series data and other Time Series Aggregate functions.

Teradata provides an ODBC driver and an analytic library for R that can be loaded into the client R environment. The R library package tdplyr conforms and works with the verbs and functions of the dplyr and dbplyr libraries.
The tdplyr in-database analytic functions that execute using the Advanced SQL Engine . Available in Vantage 1.1 or later.
The Context Manager in Teradata R Package allows programs written in R to interact directly with objects in the Teradata Database through programatically defined "context".

Teradata provides an ODBC driver and an analytic library for R that can be loaded into the client R environment. The R library package tdplyr conforms and works with the verbs and functions of the dplyr and dbplyr libraries.
A collection of functions that use a rule based machine learning method for discovering relationships between variables in large databases.  Part of the Machine Learning Engine Analytic functions.

A function for identifying a set of touchpoints as steps towards a specific end point, and then assigning each of those touchpoints a weighted value. Other functions used for similar purposes are time series and path analysis. Part of the Machine Learning Engine Analytic functions.

Grouping data points or objects so that each is more similar to the other objects in its group than it is to those in other groups. Each group is a reffered to as a cluster, so this practice is also called clustering. This can be accomplished with a collection of functions as part of the Machine Learning Engine Analytic functions.

A collection of functions that use a mathematical formula to modify every point in a data set. This might be done to make one data set comprable to another, to change units, etc. Part of the Machine Learning Engine Analytic functions.

A supervised learning technique that combines multiple learning algorithms to get better predictive performance than could be obtained with a single algorithm. These functions are part of the MLE Analytic functions.

Studying relationships between objects through mathematical models that represent things like communication, organization, networks, etc. A collection of these functions is part of the MLE Analytic functions.
A method of determining how likely an object is to fall into a category or classification. Commonly used in text categorization. Part of the MLE Analytic Functions.
NeuralNet is a feature that has been depricated in Vantage as of October 2019, Vantage Machine Learning Engine release number 1.0, 8.00. It mostly applies to small and simple use cases.
A statistical techniqe to evaluate causal relationships or dependencies among variables.  These functions are part of the MLE Analytic functions.
The practice of identifying patterns and trends in data including percentile, correlation, histogram and distribution. A collection of these functions is part of the MLE Analytic functions.

Discovery of patterns, key terms, and sentiment from text-based data. For example, you can create a word cloud to extract the most common terms used in product reviews.  These functions are part of the MLE Analytic functions.

Analysis of an ordered sequence of measurements of a variable that are arranged according to the time of occurrence. Time series are typically measured at some constant frequency and the data points are generally, but not necessarily, spaced at uniform time intervals.

An analytic tool that provides access to Vantage. Jupyter is an open-source web application that allows you to create and share documents that contain live code, equations, visualizations, and narrative text using notebooks. Teradata provides SQL extensions for Jupyter
An analytic tool that provides access to Vantage. RStudio is an IDE for R. In addition to a console and editor, RStudio includes tools for plotting, history, debugging, and workspace management.
Allows you to define your own compression and decompression algorithms and apply them to data at the column level.
A lossless, dictionary-based compression scheme at the column level
Provides an interface to functions using standard HTTPS requests.
A consumer operator to load a large volume of data at high speed into an empty table in the database.
The extended MultiLoad (MlaodX) protocol is an alternative way to load data into a target table when the traditional MultiLoad protocol cannot be used because of a restriction on the target table.
An efficient way to deal with batch maintenance of large databases. A command-driven utility for fast, high-volume maintenance on multiple tables and views in a database.

A row partition consists of 0 or more rows of a table or join index that have the same value for the partitioning expressions defined for the database object. The primary advantage presented by row partitioning is using row partition elimination as an aid to optimizing queries made on row-partitioned database objects.
Data type used for storing and accessing multidimensional data. The ARRAY data type can store many values of the same specific data type in a sequential or matrix-like format.
Represents a large binary string of raw bytes. A binary large object (BLOB) column can store binary objects, such as graphics, video clips, files, and documents.
Represents a large character string. A character large object (CLOB) column can store character data, such as simple text or HTML.

A complex data type (CDT) representing self-describing files that are interpreted based on a schema. Teradata support includes the DATASET data type and the functions and methods available for processing, shredding, and publishing DATASET data.

FEATURE_NAME: Dataset Data Type Storage Format CSV
FEATURE_NOTES: Each DATASET use must specify a storage format. The STORAGE FORMAT syntax was extended to support the DATASET data type. Teradata Database provides built-in CSV storage formats for the DATASET data type.
A UDT (user defined data type) that is based on a single predefined data type, such as INTEGER or VARCHAR.
With dot notation, also called entity reference, you can traverse a JSON document and retrieve individual JSON entities.

JSON (Javascript Object Notation) is a data interchange format, often used in web applications to transmit data. JSON documents can be stored and processed in Teradata Vantage using the JSON data type.
A data type that represents a numeric value with optional precision and scale limitations.
Sets the active transform group for Complex Data Types (CDTs) that have multiple transform groups.
Driver retrieves many small LOBs without sending any additional queries,
A user defined data type (UDT) with a collection of one or more fields called attributes, where each attribute is defined as a predefined data type or other UDT
The UDT data type represents a custom data type for modeling the structure and behavior of real-world entities used by applications.
XML data type that allows you to store XML content in a compact binary form that preserves the information set of the XML document
During nPath analysis, one can create symbol predicates that compare a row to a previous or subsequent row, using a LAG or LEAD operator.
PIVOT is a relational operator for transforming rows into columns. The function is useful for reporting purposes, as it allows you to aggregate and rotate data to create easy-to-read tables.

UNPIVOT is the reverse of the PIVOT operation. It provides a mechanism for transforming columns into rows. The UNPIVOT functionality was introduced previously via the TD_UNPIVOT table operator. Note: UNPIVOT invokes the TD_UNPIVOT table operator internally. You can still use TD_UNPIVOT independent of UNPIVOT.
A combination of several same-type JOIN, SUM, or RET query steps from multiple sources that have been combined as a single-step optimization.
Scalar sub-queries (SSQ) are sub-query expressions that result in a single value.
Calculates attributions with a wide range of distribution models. Often used in web-page analysis, where it lets companies assign weights to pages before certain events, such as buying a product.
Computes average values in a series.
Tokenizes (splits) an input stream and emits n multigrams, based on specified delimiter and reset parameters. Useful for sentiment analysis, topic identification, and document classification.
A function that scans a set of rows, looking for specified patterns. For each set of input rows that matches the pattern, nPath produces a single output row.
Maps each click in a clickstream to a unique session identifier. A session is a sequence of clicks by one user that are separated by at most n seconds.

BUSINESS_VALUE_DESC: Data recovery via restore from backup

FEATURE_NOTES: Partitioning stores related groups of data in physical proximity to improve the performance of queries that are likely to require that data.  Row partitioning allows sets of rows to be stored in separate partitions, and column partitioning allows sets of columns (including just a single column) to be stored in separate partitions.
Column-partitioned tables and column-partitioned join indexes can be defined without a primary index
Column-partitioned tables and join indexes can have a Primary AMP indexing method
Column-partitioned tables and join indexes can have a Primary Index method

The term Teradata Columnar describes tables with a Primary Index (PI), Primary AMP Index (PA), or No Primary Index (NoPI) that are column-partitioned. It is a physical database design implementation that consists of an integrated set of options that support column partitioning, columnar storage, autocompression, and other capabilities that you can specify for column-partitioned tables.

NoPI tables are permanent tables that do not have primary indexes defined on them. They provide a performance advantage when used as staging tables to load data from FastLoad or TPump Array INSERT. They can have secondary indexes defined on them to avoid full-table scans during row access.
Tables that allow duplicate rows.

Obtain view column information using DBC.Columnsq and DBC.Columnsjq. Access the information in the following views from a SELECT statement, and the result set is joinable to information in other views and tables
A table where duplicate rows are not permitted.

FEATURE_NAME: Soft RetLimit for number of rows AMP step returns

FEATURE_NOTES: Support to Teradata Database for three dimensional geospatial coordinate data. The feature includes a geospatial data type, minimum bounding box (MBB),that adds z-coordinate support to existing geospatial methods, and adds new methods specific to three dimensional data.

Tools and database objects (including data types, functions, and methods) that provide an interface between Teradata Database and applications that manage, analyze, and display geographic information.
Teradata Database supports creation of nonunique secondary indexes (NUSIs) on predicates using the geospatial method for distance, which returns the distance between two ST_Geometry values.
Teradata Database supports creation of nonunique secondary indexes (NUSIs) on geospatial data columns.

FEATURE_NAME: Geospatial Index Single Table Distance Predicate
FEATURE_NOTES: Predicates that use the ST_Distance and ST_3DDistance methods and cause the optimizer to evaluate a geospatial index, if one exists, as a potential access path to the geospatial data. In these circumstances, the index can greatly speed access to the data and execution of the query.

Predicates that cause the optimizer to evaluate a geospatial index, if one exists, as a potential access path to the geospatial data. In these circumstances, the index can greatly speed access to the data and execution of the query.
Enables multiple active Teradata systems to work as one, managing database changes and query routing to automatically coordinate and maintain order and consistency across the environment.
Vantage provides a set of embedded services system functions that support byte/bit manipulation.
Provides a way to use remote data source, rather than the Teradata Database, to process queries involving remote tables.

The trigger defines events that happen when some other event, called a triggering event, occurs. This database object is essentially a stored SQL statement associated with a table called a subject table.

Join indexes are file structures designed to permit queries (join queries in the case of multitable join indexes) to be resolved by accessing the index instead of having to access and join their underlying base tables.

FEATURE_NAME: In-Memory All Rows One AMP Optimization
Binary Join Push for Union All
InList Rewrite disqualifed by MultiTable Expression
Push TOP N into UNION ALL Derived Tables

FEATURE_NOTES: A table or join index may be column partitioned, row partitioned, or both, by using multilevel partitioning. Multilevel partitioning allows each partition to be subpartitioned. Each level must define at least two partitions.

Queries can contain Named Parameters, making it easy to reuse a query because the only changes are the data values (for example, in a Where clause). Named Parameters function like variables. Enter the value for a named parameter once. If it is used in multiple places within the query, the same value is used in all places.

Collects demographic data for one or more columns of a base table, hash index, or join index, computes a statistical profile of the collected data, and stores the synopsis in the Data Dictionary. The Optimizer uses the synopsis data when it generates its table access and join plans.
External stored procedures are written in the C, C++, or Java programming language, installed on the database, and then executed like stored procedures.
The ability to run functions on a foreign server. The output of the HELP FOREIGN FUNCTION command shows detailed information about the ML Engine function specified.

In-database support for R program execution. Data stored in Teradata databases can be directly accessed by the R execution engine for analysis. R scripts are executed in parallel inside the database using the system table operator ExecR.
Table operators accept a table or table expression as input and generate a table as output. The SCRIPT table operator executes a user-installed script or any LINUX command inside the database.

A table function is invoked in the FROM clause of an SQL SELECT statement and returns a table, a row at a time in a loop to the SELECT statement. The function can produce the rows of a table from the input arguments passed to it or by reading an external file or message queue.

You can create user-defined table operators, which accept one or more tables or table expressions as input and generate a table as output. A table operator is a form of UDF that can only be specified in the FROM clause of a SELECT statement.

Called Persistent Stored Modules in the ANSI/ISO SQL:2008 standard. They are written in SQL and consist of a set of control and condition handling statements that make SQL a computationally complete programming language. These features provide a server-based procedural interface to the database for application programmers. Teradata stored procedure facilities are a subset of and conform to the ANSI/ISO SQL:2008 standards for semantics.
UDFs allow you to extend SQL by writing your own functions.
Removes unnecessary remote tables from queries.
Provides a way to use the remote data source, rather than the Teradata Database, to process queries involving remote tables.

External authentication allows Teradata Database users to be authenticated by an agent running on the same network as Teradata Database and its clients. Teradata Database supports single-sign on (SSO) and directory access (LDAP).

One way of controlling access to tables and views. Teradata row level security controls user access by row and by SQL operation. Access rules are based on the relationship between the user access level and the row security level.
A Period data type represents a time period, where a period is a set of contiguous time granules that extends from a beginning bound up to but not including an ending bound.

Teradata introduced support for creating and manipulating temporal tables before an ANSI/ISO standard had been developed. Consequently, the original Teradata temporal tables and SQL syntax do not conform to the ANSI standard. Both the ANSI compliant and original non-ANSI compliant versions of temporal tables are available in Vantage.

Time series data is stored in a specialized table that contains a structure called a primary time index (PTI). Time series data is unstructured machine-generated sensor data that is continuously produced and collected by a wide range of applications and devices.
